body:
Minimal example demonstrating the bug:

```
function integer fun;
integer array[0:0];
begin
    array[0] = 10;
    fun = array[0];
end
endfunction

module test ();
begin
    localparam something = fun();
end
endmodule
```

Changing to `fun = 10; //array[0];` works.

Command used:

`docker run -it -v/tmp:/tmp --rm verilator/verilator:v5.032 --cc /tmp/test.v`

OS: Ubuntu 18.04.6 LTS with Docker version 24.0.2

This is a regression as it used to work before.
